  plantName: Ranunculus Flower
  description: Ranunculus is a large genus of roughly 1,750 species of flowering
    plants in the family Ranunculaceae, often known as buttercups, spearworts, or
    water crowfoots. Popularly known as Persian Buttercups, they are prized for their
    rose-like, multi-layered petals, appearing in a rainbow of colors including white,
    yellow, pink, and red.
